\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}  \frac{n}{2^n}
\displaystyle \lim_{x\to \infty}\frac{\frac{n+1}{2^{n+1}}}{\frac{n}{2^{n}}}=\lim_{x\to \infty}\frac{n+1}{2n}=\frac 1 2<0
\displaystyle\sum_{n=1}^\infty \frac n {2^n}
\displaystyle S=\sum_{n=1}^\infty \frac n {2^n}=\frac 1 2 + \frac 2 {2^2} + \frac 3 {2^3}+...
